    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRAZIL TRADE DATA STRENGTHENS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's trade deficit narrowed in $1.62 billion in May from $3.08 billion in April; rising confidence in Brazilian economy leads to increase in direct investment in Brazil by multinational companies, to $1.77 billion from $1.36 billion in April (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The broadest measure of Brazilian trade showed the lowest deficit in three months in May, reflecting the strength of Brazilian export growth. The deficit, which narrowed to $1.62 billion from $3.08 billion in April, also reflected a drop in interest payments on government bonds. Rising confidence in the Brazilian economy also led to an increase in direct investment in Brazil by multinational companies, to $1.77 billion from $1.36 billion in April.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
